O'Brien Upsets Siemerink to Win Pilot Pen Tennis 
Alex O'Brien, who ranked 169 in the world, beat 10th-seeded Jan
Siemerink 7-6 (8-6), 6-4 in the final of the Pilot Pen International in
New Haven, the United States, Sunday.
Before the final, O'Brien defeated three other seeded players - No. 8
Arnaud Boetsch, No. 1 Yevgeny Kafelnikov and No. 14 Mark Philippoussis.
The 26-year-old American, the 1992 U.S. college singles and doubles
champion, earned dlrs 150,000.
